verbose_text: Hence in the present study, the defensive role of GG against MG was elucidated and the results showed that the indicative decrease in the levels of RAGE (2.4-fold) and NF-kappaB (1.7-fold) were observed in GG pre-treated cells exposed to MG, suggesting that aggressive cataract development is routed via key NF-kappaB signaling (XREF_FIG).
